                <div class="field-group">
                    <label class="field-label" for="splitType">Step 3: How many days can you lift weights per week?</label>
                    <p class="field-description">We'll design your schedule to optimize recovery and progress</p>
                    <select class="dropdown" id="splitType">
                        <option value="3-day-full-body">3 Days - Full Body Split (Beginners/Busy Athletes)</option>
                        <option value="3-day-upper-lower">3 Days - Upper/Lower Split (Low Recoverability)</option>
                        <option value="4-day-full-body">4 Days - Full Body Split (High Recoverability)</option>
                        <option value="4-day-upper-lower">4 Days - Upper/Lower Split (Most Popular)</option>
                    </select>
                    <span class="toggle-technical" onclick="toggleTechnical('split-tech')">Show technical details</span>
                    <div class="technical-details technical-note" id="split-tech">
                        <strong>Technical terms:</strong> High/Low alternates high CNS days with recovery days. Upper/Lower splits body parts. Full Body trains the upper and lower body in each session.
                    </div>
                </div>

